Change has been successfully merged by Cody Peter Mello
What's the license for all this?
The tests don't ship with a license. On his website ( http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~bwk/btl.mirror/ ) he states: "Awk test files; use at your own risk."
If these came from GNU, then we need a third party license file in here for those portions.
I've added THIRDPARTYLICENSE.gawk with the GPLv3 text.
General shell style matches C style so a tab character for indentation + 4 character continuations.
Done
Today none of the scripts in general illumos rely on bash. Can this also work with ksh?

I've updated this script and some of the others to use ksh, but some of them don't currently work with ksh, primarily due to differences in escaping behaviour. I can modify the tests as needed if not relying on bash is a hard requirement.
OK, how about you have this script check for bash and skip the tests otherwise, but keep it in ksh? If it came from GNU expecting bash, it'll probably be easier to just require bash for this.
I've kept this script ksh, and reverted the others back to bash.
Please use updated CDDL header in prototypes/
Done
Please don't run this from the proto area. That's almost never correct. This should be designed like the other tests and integrated into the text runner.
This now points at /usr/bin/nawk by default, and I've set it up to install with util-tests.
this should probably be fatal, no? I don't think you want to continue executing the test.
Yes, there should be an exit here. I've added an "exit 1".
Spurious whitespace?
Fixed.
Maybe we should search $PATH for bash rather than assuming its actual location?

I checked the actual location since that's what's in the shebang, but I could change the shebang to:

    #!/usr/bin/env bash
Based on further conversation. I think it probably is fine to just go ahead and start with how things are.
